The Closure library right now has this in goog.fs.Error:

goog.fs.Error = function(...) {
  ...

  /**
   * @type {goog.fs.Error.ErrorCode}
   * @deprecated Use the 'name' or 'message' field instead.
   */
  this.code;
}

and we get a deprecation warning even though we never read the 'code' field. I think the compiler is treating that 'this.code' line as though it's reading the variable, but really it's just declaring it. We should not warn about the deprecation in this case.
